<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>CSS Typography</title>
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-family: "Georgia", serif;
      font-size: 36px;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-align: center;
    }

    p {
      font-family: "Arial", sans-serif;
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      word-spacing: 5px;
      text-align: justify;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Typography Example</h1>
  <p>
    Typography in CSS helps make the text more readable and visually appealing. 
    We can change font family, size, weight, spacing, and alignment to improve design.
  </p>

</body>
</html>
